Mining company leases in Vanuatu show Slaughter of birds
Oxfam says it has evidence that mining companies are violating nature reserves, slaughtering protected tree species and importing people who must be resettled from the sites of their future operations. The organisation’s records of what it calls “land grabs” amounts to 55 leases across 25 islands in Vanuatu. The assessment was drawn from internal information in companies call logs and found for some areas a lack of land tenure and knowledge of relevant legal frameworks.
